ss=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#70DB93>(12/23/01 7:26:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~deprugh/brimface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why?</span><hr size=1> A more important question is ...<br><br>Why did they choose to reduce the quality of game play by adding new graphics that would require more than 3/4 of its player base to either upgrade their computers or cancel their account? Why add graphics when the current graphics were already better than anything out there? Maybe they are RL loot whores.<br><br>I bought a new computer in march 1999 to play EQ, upgraded it for Velious and WONT upgrade again. They made a stupid statement about 256MB Ram not costing a lot of money, not thinking about the fact that MOST of the computers out there have a CMOS that will not accept them (only see 128mb of the 256mb). <br><br>Be well and have a Wonderful Holiday Season.<br><br><br><br> <p><center><img src="http://home.mindspring.com/~deprugh/brimage-new.gif" height=150 border=0></a><br><font size=+2 color="green">The GREEN Midget</font><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45542" target="_new">Inspect me here</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ugyre1227.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyre1227</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#70DB93>(12/23/01 9:33:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why?</span><hr size=1> I think it even more odd how it varies from system to system.  I have a 600mhz celeron laptop with max ram 192.  The Video takes its ram from the system ram for a max of 8 mb for video.  This system has run the game better then my desktop at 550 mhz with 768mb of ram and geforce 3 64 mb card.  Hopefully they get all the bugs out soon, I notice more improvement everytime they patch and that Texture Cache made a huge difference on all my systems. <p>Nendyina WxElemental<br>L53 Elementalist<br><br>Cildyin Panacea<br>L27 Cleric<br><br>Officer of the Risen Phoenix</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ufilumtil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filumtil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Federation Admin</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#70DB93>(12/24/01 1:29:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.camelot.de/~ekraemer/filumtil3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /shrug</span><hr size=1> Had severe problems right at the start for about a week, but none at all now; except for the slightly longer zoning time it's all back to normal. Duron 800, 512 MB, Geforce 3, Win 98 SE (perhaps the most important factor) - by no means an &quot;uber&quot;-PC.<br><br>Kalina, you're not forced to install the update, just revert back to Velious or Kunark - the graphics will be OK again, and you'll not have to put up with plots you don't like. BTW, where is there Sci-Fi? There's no science at all there, just normal magic. All places I saw so far were extremely in line with the old EQ, but heck, it's the MOON we're talking about, of course life evolved slightly different there. As to why you can't update your EZboard... that's probably one thing where VI is not at fault. :-)<br><br>Brimztone, they *reduced* the quality?! Have you ever run through the old world zones with the new textures? The quality has been boosted a LOT, at least my little gnome eyes perceive the world a lot sharper now (Freeport, for example). Again, if the new textures are giving your PC problems, revert to Velious, and you'll have the old textures again.<br><br>Grumble grumble,<br>Filumtil Applepie<br>Necromancer of the 53rd crypt <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ufilumtil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filumtil</A> at: 12/24/01 1:44:33 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showMessage?topicID=132.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showMessage?topicID=137.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=138.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.threadControl?topicID=138.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=138.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a 